    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect packet loss calculation in OTG KPI metrics\n\n### Summary\nThe `otg_kpi_nb_loss_pkts()` function in the OTG module was overcounting background traffic packet losses by a factor of MAX_EMU_TRAFFIC (typically 10x). This occurred because the function was adding background loss counters inside the application type loop, causing each background loss to be counted once per application rather than once per source-destination pair.\n\nThis led to inflated total loss metrics in the OTG KPI reports, affecting simulation accuracy for scenarios with background traffic enabled. Users observed unexpectedly high packet loss rates in their performance evaluations.\n\nThe issue is resolved by separating the background loss accumulation from the per-application loss accumulation, ensuring each background loss is counted exactly once.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OTG/otg_kpi.c`: Modified `otg_kpi_nb_loss_pkts()` to correctly accumulate background losses once per (src,dst) pair and regular traffic losses per application type.\n\n"
}